<h1>Problem 255 - 2017 IMOSL, A4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>A sequence of real numbers \(a_1, a_2, \dots\) satisfies the relation \[a_n = - \max_{i+j=n} \left( a_i + a_j \right) \qquad \text{ for all } n > 2017.\]Prove that this sequence is bounded, i.e., there is a constant \(M\) such that \(\left \lvert a_n \right \rvert \leq M\) for all positive integers \(n\).</p>
